<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-21 00:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moderate Quakes Rock Taiwan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) -- Three moderate earthquake shook central
Taiwan Monday, a day after a series of temblors rattled the area.
No injuries or damages were immediately reported.
</P>
<P>
   The three earthquakes -- from 4.0 to 4.6 in magnitude -- struck in
succession at about 3 a.m. around Taoyuan city, about 125 miles
south of the capital, Taipei, the Central Weather Bureau said.
</P>
<P>
   On Sunday, five earthquakes shook central Taiwan. The strongest
was a 4.6-magnitude temblor about 8.4 miles southeast of Hualien
city at 10:17 p.m., the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
   Taiwan is often hit by tremors as it sits atop two tectonic
plates, huge, moving slabs of the Earth's crust.
</P>
<P>
   Thousands of minor tremors and aftershocks have rattled Taiwan
since a 7.6-magnitude quake devastated parts of central Taiwan in
September, killing about 2,400 people and destroying thousands of
homes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
