<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-21 01:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Killed in Austria Bus Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   VIENNA, Austria (AP) -- At least seven people, including
children, were killed or severely injured early Monday when a semi
truck crashed into a tour bus carrying German tourists towards
Vienna, local media said.
</P>
<P>
   A semi jumped the median and rammed into the bus, splitting it
open, Austrian state radio said. At least seven people were killed
and others severely injured, it said.
</P>
<P>
   Police told the Austria Press Agency that mostly children and
young people were aboard the German bus, and ''several'' had been
killed while others were severely injured. They declined to give
exact numbers.
</P>
<P>
   Neither of the reports could be independently confirmed.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred near Melk, 55 miles west of Vienna.
</P>
<P>
   No further information was immediately available.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
