<HEADLINE> Gates Competes in Bridge Tournament  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Microsoft Chairman Bill Gates put his
cards on the table as he played in the final rounds of the North
American Bridge Championships.
</P>
<P>
   Microsoft spokesman John Pinette confirmed that Gates was
participating Sunday, but said he didn't know how he had fared.
</P>
<P>
   Gates' partner, Sharon Osberg of San Francisco, and teammates
Sheri Weinstock of Toronto and Howard Weinstein of Chicago just
managed to reach the finals on Saturday, garnering a total of 27
points in qualifying sessions. The cutoff score was 26.5.
</P>
<P>
   Although this is the first time he has played in a national
championship, Gates is a longtime online bridge player and his
performance in the finals has been impressive, tournament officials
said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Gates has done remarkably well in this tournament,'' said
American Contract Bridge League spokesman Michael Calhoun. ''His
partners have enjoyed his passion for the game.''
</P>
<P>
   ''The game is so deep,'' Gates said in a statement. ''There's
always something you can learn.''
</P>
</TEXT>
