<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 30; Nasdaq Climbs 36  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are higher in early trading. The
Dow Jones industrial average is up about 30 points. Advancing
issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a slim lead over
decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 36 points and the
Standard-and-Poor's 500 Stock Index is up six points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street is in waiting mode, ahead of tomorrow's Federal
Reserve meeting. While there's virtually unanimous agreement that
the central bank won't hike rates, analysts want to see if the Fed
gives any clue how it feels about the economic climate.
</P>
<P>
   There's not much else on the economic calendar or on the
earnings front scheduled this week to provide the market with
excitement. Keep an eye on shares of Intel, which is holding a
technology forum. It is slated to unveil its Pentium four
microprocessors.
</P>
</TEXT>
