<HEADLINE> Bodies Recovered From Chile Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) -- Rescue crews battling strong wind on
Monday recovered the bodies of 14 victims, including six children,
who died in an army plane crash in southern Chile two weeks ago,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Commandos reached the area by land and cleared a spot for the
landing of an air force helicopter, which brought out the bodies,
air force Col. Alejandro Salas said.
</P>
<P>
   The Spanish-made Casa T212 crashed Aug. 6 while flying in a
storm near Chaiten, 890 miles south of Santiago. The wreckage was
located Sunday night. Salas said the aircraft was ''badly
destroyed.''
</P>
<P>
   The aircraft was carrying two crew members and six children ages
2 to 13, all relatives of army personnel.
</P>
</TEXT>
