<HEADLINE> Networks Winning With Tiger  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Tiger Woods keeps winning, and so do the
networks that televise golf's major tournaments.
</P>
<P>
   Woods' duel with Bob May at the PGA Championship drew the
event's highest preliminary TV ratings on record.
</P>
<P>
   CBS's coverage of Sunday's final round, when Woods finally put
away May in a three-hole playoff, got a big-market rating of 10.0
with a 23 share. That means about 10 million homes tuned in, and 23
percent of TVs that were on during the broadcast were tuned to CBS.
</P>
<P>
   The rating was 30 percent higher than it was for last year's
PGA, when Woods beat Spanish sensation Sergio Garcia by a single
stroke. The 1999 rating had been the best for a final round PGA
since at least 1986.
</P>
</TEXT>
