<HEADLINE> Rocker Nugent, Rep. Barr Team Up  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MARIETTA, Ga. (AP) -- On the surface, they seem like an odd pair
-- conservative Rep. Bob Barr and long-haired rocker Ted Nugent.
</P>
<P>
   But Barr and Nugent are both board members of the National Rifle
Association and outspoken defenders of the right to bear arms.
</P>
<P>
   Nugent made his point as loudly as one of his guitar solos
Sunday during a fund-raiser for Barr.
</P>
<P>
   ''The right to life means not dying,'' Nugent told a crowd of
mostly hunters and sportsmen. ''What does that mean? When someone
wants to take your life, shoot him.''
</P>
<P>
   About 1,000 people paid $25 apiece for a barbecue dinner and an
archery demonstration from Nugent, who took aim at foam replicas of
a grizzly bear and a deer.
</P>
<P>
   Nugent is best known for his 1977 album and song ''Cat Scratch
Fever.''
