<HEADLINE> Fuel Spilled in Siberian River  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW (AP) -- An accident on a river barge in the Siberian city
of Omsk spilled about 50 tons of diesel fuel into the Irtysh River
Monday, a transport official said.
</P>
<P>
   Cleanup crews contained the spill and there was little threat to
the river's ecosystem, said Alexey Belozerov, a spokesman for the
Interior Ministry's transport police division.
</P>
<P>
   Transport police were looking into whether workers had properly
closed a valve on the vessel's storage tanks before filling them
with fuel, Belozerov said.
</P>
<P>
   Oil and fuel leaks are common in Russia. The environmental group
Greenpeace has said that between 11 million and 22 million tons of
oil leaks annually in small accidents. Russia produces about 330
million tons of oil a year.
</P>
</TEXT>
