<HEADLINE> Two Atlantic County brothers charged in killing on Lindenwold train platform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) - Two Atlantic County brothers were charged
with murder Monday in the killing of a man they fought with on a
train platform in Lindenwold, Prosecutor Lee A. Solomon said.
</P>
<P>
   A third suspect was being sought, Solomon said.
</P>
<P>
   The three had a fight Thursday with the victim, Wayne Biscardi,
and another man at the NJ Transit train platform, Solomon said.
Biscardi, 33, of Atlantic City, was beaten, kicked and knocked off
the platform to the tracks below by the three men, Solomon said.
</P>
<P>
   He suffered serious head injuries and was admitted to Kennedy
Memorial Hospital in Stratford, where he died Saturday, Solomon
said.
</P>
<P>
   Peter Marzano, 28, of Pleasantville; and his brother, David S.
Marzano, 26, of Egg Harbor Township, were arrested Thursday and
charged with aggravated assault. Those charges were upgraded to
murder Monday, Solomon said.
</P>
<P>
   They are being held in the Camden County Jail in lieu of $75,000
bail.
</P>
<P>
   The third suspect, also of Atlantic County, is being sought.
Solomon declined to identify him.
</P>
<P>
   The man who was with Biscardi received minor injuries in the
fight. Solomon did not identify him.
</P>
