<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UCLA Makes Paus Starting QB  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Cory Paus, who started seven games for UCLA
last year before breaking his collarbone and undergoing
season-ending surgery, will open the season as the Bruins' No. 1
quarterback again.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Bob Toledo gave Paus the nod over fellow sophomore Ryan
McCann.
</P>
<P>
   ''Cory, at this point, operates the offense better and that was
the whole key,'' Toledo said Monday. ''Ryan is still learning and
he's made great strides and he's closed the gap a little. He just
doesn't have the total knowledge of the offense that Cory does at
this point.''
</P>
<P>
   McCann came off the bench to spark the Bruins to a 23-20
overtime victory over Washington late last season, but was less
impressive the following week in a 17-7 loss to Southern
California.
</P>
<P>
   Junior Scott McEwan is listed as the No. 3 quarterback.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA, unranked in the preseason, opens the season Sept. 2
against preseason No. 3 Alabama at the Rose Bowl.
</P>
</TEXT>
