UCLA Makes Paus Starting QB
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Cory Paus, who started seven games for UCLA last year
before breaking his collarbone and undergoing season-ending surgery, will open
the season as the Bruins' No. 1 quarterback again. Coach Bob Toledo gave Paus
the nod over fellow sophomore Ryan McCann. UCLA, unranked in the preseason,
opens the season Sept. 2 against preseason No. 3 Alabama at the Rose Bowl.
</P>
