<HEADLINE> Man struck and killed by commuter train  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) - A man was struck and killed by a New
York-bound train three minutes after it left Long Branch Monday,
authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The man was walking with a woman when he was struck by the New
Jersey Transit's North Jersey Coast Line train at 2:51 p.m., agency
spokesman Michael Klufas said. The train had left Long Branch at
2:48 p.m., Klufas said.
</P>
<P>
   Klufas was unsure whether the man, whose name has not been
released, was on or beside the tracks. His companion was being
questioned, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Klufas wasn't sure how fast the train was going or whether the
engineer sounded a warning horn before the man was hit.
</P>
</TEXT>
