<HEADLINE> Devil Rays' Williams Hits Homer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Tampa Bay's Gerald Williams became the 25th
player in major league history to hit 20 home runs from the leadoff
spot Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Williams hit his 20th with one out in the third inning, a solo
shot, off Chicago's Jim Parque. The Devil Rays outfielder is the
14th player in the American League to accomplish the feat.
</P>
<P>
   Baltimore's Brady Anderson and San Francisco's Bobby Bonds have
the most leadoff homers in the majors with 35 each set in 1996 and
1973, respectively.
</P>
<P>
   Williams' previous career high in home runs was 17, set last
year with Atlanta.
</P>
