<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Hurricanes' Tyler Suspended  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) -- Miami forward Elton Tyler has been
suspended for the fall semester for academic reasons and will miss
at least six games, according to The Palm Beach Post.
</P>
<P>
   Tyler, one of two starters returning from the team that reached
the regional semifinals of the NCAA tournament last season, will
not be eligible to play until at least mid-December, the newspaper
reported in Tuesday's editions, citing unnamed school sources.
</P>
<P>
   Tyler could become eligible for the Hurricanes' Dec. 16 game
against Nebraska in the Orange Bowl Classic.
</P>
<P>
   The newspaper was unable to reach Tyler on Monday, but said his
mother, Eleanor Tyler of Dorchester, Mass., was unaware of any
problems.
</P>
<P>
   ''I spoke to him yesterday on the telephone and he didn't say
anything about that,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   The newspaper did not have details of the academic violation,
but said it preceded Perry Clark's hiring as coach July 6. Clark
replaced Leonard Hamilton, who became coach of the NBA's Washington
Wizards.
</P>
<P>
   Clark was traveling Monday and could not be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-9 Tyler averaged 10.1 points and 5.5 rebounds last
season, when the Hurricanes finished 23-11 and won the Big East
Conference regular-season championship. He led the Hurricanes in
shooting at 51.2 percent and in blocked shots with 34.
</P>
<P>
   The school's sports information director did not immediately
return calls to his home Monday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
